==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Martinmas
<hw>Mar"tin*mas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[St. <ets>Martin +
mass</ets> religious service.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The feast
of <person>St. Martin</person>, the eleventh of November; -- often
called <altname>martlemans</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Martinmas summer</b></col>, <cd>a period of calm, warm
weather often experienced about the time of Martinmas; Indian
summer.</cd> <rj><au>Percy Smith.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martite</ent>⟦br⟧
